cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with object edge detection and classification in images, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel strategy for solving this problem using neural net classifiers, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG - Machine Learning). The paper also uses backpropagation and visualization algorithms, which are techniques used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI - Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of large bounding boxes, which is a technique used in neural networks (cs.NE - Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with image processing techniques, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM - Multimedia).
